qas.question: How many immigrants were in Paris in 2012 from Europe?
How many immigrants to Paris in 2012 were from the Maghreb?
How many immigrants in Paris in 2012 were from sub-Saharan Africa and Egypt?
How many Asians immigrated to Paris in 2012?

context: The remaining group, people born in foreign countries with no French citizenship at birth, are those defined as immigrants under French law. According to the 2012 census, <a0_0>135,853<a0_0/> residents of the city of Paris were immigrants from Europe, <a1_0>112,369<a1_0/> were immigrants from the Maghreb, <a2_0>70,852<a2_0/> from sub-Saharan Africa and Egypt, 5,059 from Turkey, <a3_0>91,297<a3_0/> from Asia (outside Turkey), 38,858 from the Americas, and 1,365 from the South Pacific. Note that the immigrants from the Americas and the South Pacific in Paris are vastly outnumbered by migrants from French overseas regions and territories located in these regions of the world.
